<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-160-076 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 707 549</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 6 1991 v8 n18 p57(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SQL Solutions gateways expand SQL server access.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pallatto, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   SQL Solutions Inc. (Product development).andO;Product:   SQL Server (Data base management system) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentGateways (Interface)Software packagesRelational data basesStructured Query LanguageConnectivity.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By John PallattoandM;SQL Solutions Inc. has constructed a set of communications gateways forSybase SQL Server, paving the way for corporate developers to access datastored in a quartet of relational databases.andM;SQL Solutions is rolling out a smorgasbord of gateways for Digital EquipmentCorp.'s Rdb, Informix Software Inc.'s Informix, Oracle Corp.'s Oracle and theIngres database from the Ingres Products Division of Ask Computer SystemsInc., according to Dan Cronin, vice president of marketing for SQL Solutions,in Burlington, Mass.andM;The gateways will allow users of Sybase SQL Server to retrieve and update thesupported databases as easily as if the information were stored in anotherSQL Server database, Cronin explained.andP;  The gateways translate the variousSQL dialects into a format that can be processed by the SQL Serverapplication, and end users work with standard SQL commands -- includingSelect, Insert, Update and Delete -- to manipulate data in the foreigndatabases.andM;&quot;Upwards of 20 to 30 percent of the corporate sites we work with havemultiple databases from different vendors running in one corporate divisionor another,&quot; he said.andM;With the gateways, developers can integrate the data stored in variousrelational databases without having to rewrite or scrap their existingapplications, Cronin said.andP;  The gateway family is based on Sybase's OpenServer application programming interface, which provides SQL Serverapplications with direct access to non-Sybase database files andapplications, he explained.andM;Gateways for Oracle, Ingres and Rdb running on VAX/VMS and Unix platformswere shipped at the end of April, according to Cronin.andP;  The gateway forInformix is being beta tested and will be ready for shipment in June, hesaid.andM;Given customer demand, SQL Solutions is gearing up to deliver OS/2 versionsof the gateways within a year, Cronin said.andM;Prices for the gateways range from $5,000 to $60,000, depending on machineclasses and database configurations.andP;  All the gateways are available directlyfrom the firm.andM;SQL Solutions, a subsidiary of Sybase Inc., has 190 employees in 16 cities inthe United States and Canada.andP;  The consulting company specializes in databaseapplication development and connectivity.andM;The firm's headquarters can be reached at (617) 270-4150.andO;</TEXT></DOC>